      • apptIsAvailable

        public static java.lang.Boolean apptIsAvailable​(java.time.ZonedDateTime zonedStartDT,
                                                java.time.ZonedDateTime zonedEndDT,
                                                java.time.LocalDate apptDate,
                                                java.time.LocalTime startTime,
                                                java.time.LocalTime endTime,
                                                java.lang.String customerID,
                                                java.lang.String contactID)
        This method checks for appointment availability. The method checks the start and end dates for availability for the customer and contact that are passed in.
        Parameters:
        startTime - the start time of the Appointment
        endTime - the end time of the Appointment
        apptDate - the Appointment date
        zonedStartDT - the zoned Appointment start date
        zonedEndDT - the zoned Appointment end date
        customerID - the Customer ID in question
        contactID - the Contact ID in question
        Returns:
        whether the appointment time slot is available.

      • apptIsUpdateable

        public static java.lang.Boolean apptIsUpdateable​(java.time.ZonedDateTime zonedStartDT,
                                                 java.time.ZonedDateTime zonedEndDT,
                                                 java.time.LocalDate apptDate,
                                                 java.time.LocalTime startTime,
                                                 java.time.LocalTime endTime,
                                                 java.lang.String customerID,
                                                 java.lang.String contactID,
                                                 java.lang.String origApptID)
        This method checks for appointment availability. The method checks the start and end dates for availability for the customer and contact that are passed in and ignores the original appointment during the comparison.
        Parameters:
        startTime - the start time of the Appointment
        endTime - the end time of the Appointment
        apptDate - the Appointment date
        zonedStartDT - the zoned Appointment start date
        zonedEndDT - the zoned Appointment end date
        customerID - the Customer ID in question
        contactID - the Contact ID in question
        origApptID - the Appointment ID of the original Appointment
        Returns:
        whether the appointment time slot is available.
